Ths location is quickly becomming one of my favorite coffee places on K Street, and there are more than a couple.  To me the coffee and teas at most of these chain coffee places are relatively the same. What makes the difference from my perspective is the ambiance. The two or three other Starbucks locations on K Street haven't always been the best experiences for me, and I think most of it has to do with ambiance.  The last location that I went to that is just a couple blocks away has the windows situated too high, so you can't really see what is going on outside.  The couple of times that I have been to this place have been decent and I've been able to get some work done on my computer. There were only a few Customers because it is Sunday, but nevertheless  they have the music cranked up so fricken loud, that I can barely even make a phone call. I wish that the employees would be a little bit more considerate for the few people who want to do actual work. I realize entertaining the staff is also important. What to say ... Every time I come to this store, one of the baristas makes me feel like I'm trying to scam the business ... every time I ask for a refill, he asks if I've been here already and if I'll be here for the next couple hours (I didn't know that was a prerequisite to get my refill), and then when I use my own cup, and ask for a tall coffee, he grabs a cup to measure it out.  Does he think I'm just trying to get more coffee in my cup and pay a smaller amount?  Perhaps, just perhaps, some of us don't like to waste all those paper cups and covers.  Maybe he could just "eye" it and put in an approximate amount equivalent to a tall.  And you know what, if he's not sure, then put in a little more ... what's wrong with that? I find that will bring customers back.  I honestly almost never come here any more just because of the barista service.  Is it the training from the store owner?  If so, all I can say is they're cheap, cheap, cheap, and as a result they are losing customers.
